<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-26-0635 </DOCNO><TEXT>A solar heating mat is described which comprises a lower insulating member,an upper insulating member and a removable inner tube. The upper insulatingmember is transparent to solar radiation, and the tube is absorbent ofsolar radiation. The inner tube has an inlet connection and outlet connectionso that a liquid, e.g. water, can circulate through the tube and be heated.</TEXT></DOC>